      "writtenOn": "2021-06-15T22:59:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m trying to avoid an overlap between the syzkaller and syzcorpus test suites(so that the syzkaller test suite fuzzes the kernel for a specific amount of time; and the syzcorpus test suite has a different duration).\nWhile the syzkaller test suite can stay in postsubmit for perpetuity; id like to try and explore moving syzcorpus to cq if it is proves to be reliable enough in postsubmit.\n\nI assumed that having a seperate test suite would enforce that the test suites are exclusive; is there something else that should be done?",
      "parentUuid": "73c1c1ff_600bf45d",
      "revId": "b56c2ff9e5c9848e2b7293c2fa7c97ac5f3230ae",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
